honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl

Class PrinterInformation_DPL

  • java.lang.Object
    • honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl.PrinterData_DPL
      • honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl.PrinterState_DPL
        • honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl.PrinterInformation_DPL
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class PrinterInformation_DPL
extends PrinterState_DPL
    This class handles the printer system information(read-only) data from an KcQQQ and v queries as well as accessors to read the data values.

    This class supports the following possible parameters:

    ParameterDescription
    ZNSerial Number
    V1Boot 1 Version
    P1Boot 1 Part Number
    A1Boot 1 Architecture
    V2Boot 2 Version
    P2Boot 2 Part Number
    A2Boot 2 Architecture
    VERVersion Information
    A3Firmware Architecture
    AVR_VERAVR Version Information
    xAVR_VERxAVR Version Information
    0Firmware Version
    1Build Date/Time
    2Model Number
    3Current Date
    4Current Time
    5Current Epoch Time
    6Firmware Build
    7External Power Connected
    8Dot Density (dots/inch)
    9Print Head Width
    ALast Error String
    BLCD Error String 1
    CLCD Error String 2
    DLCD Error Number
    EAuto Update Error String
    FPrinter Model
    GAbsolute Counter
    HAbsolute Counter Date
    IResettable Counter
    JResettable Counter Date
    KError Script String
    LLua Current State
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

    • Constructor Detail

      • PrinterInformation_DPL

        public PrinterInformation_DPL(ConnectionBase conn)
        The default constructor will initialize the class with default values.

        Initially all of the _IsValid parameters will be false because no data has been processed. To 'populate' the values, the object must invoke @see PrinterState_DPL.queryPrinter(int) with the query response string.

        Parameters:
        conn - connection to printer
